carbon which is carbon-14.

43
00:02:14,153 --> 00:02:18,985
And carbon-14 decays
over time back into nitrogen.

44
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:21,476
So, um, what’s the ratio?

45
00:02:21,501 --> 00:02:28,178
Well we have: for every one
trillion carbon-12 atoms
there is one carbon-14 atom.

46
00:02:28,203 --> 00:02:30,333
So we know the ratio.
Okay, one trillion …

47
00:02:30,358 --> 00:02:34,707
